{"type": "root", "attrs": {"type": "node", "context": "sop", "internal": "bend", "icon": "SOP/bend", "tags": "reshape, anim, model", "since": "14.5", "version": null, "namespace": null}, "body": [{"level": 0, "type": "title", "indent": 0, "text": ["Bend"], "extent": [0, 9]}, {"type": "summary", "indent": 0, "text": ["Applies deformations to captured geometry such as bend, twist, taper, and squash/stretch."], "extent": [110, 208]}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Overview"], "extent": [208, 223], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["This node lets you define a ", {"type": "em", "text": ["capture region"]}, " around (or partially intersecting) a model, and apply deformations to the geometry inside the capture region."], "extent": [223, 380]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["The available deformations are:"], "extent": [380, 413]}, {"type": "bullet_group", "body": [{"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": "Icon", "value": "SHELF/twist_bend", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/SHELF/twist_bend"}, " Bend."], "extent": [413, 445]}, {"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": "Icon", "value": "SOP/twist", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/SOP/twist"}, " Twist."], "extent": [445, 471]}, {"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": "Icon", "value": "SHELF/twist_squashstretch", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/SHELF/twist_squashstretch"}, " Length Scale with optional volume preservation (", {"type": "q", "text": ["squash and stretch"]}, ")."], "extent": [471, 577]}, {"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": "Icon", "value": "SHELF/twist_linear_taper", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/SHELF/twist_linear_taper"}, " Liner and ", {"scheme": "Icon", "value": "SHELF/twist_taper", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/SHELF/twist_taper"}, " Smooth taper."], "extent": [577, 661]}], "container": true}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["The capture region is the space between two parallel infinite planes, defined by an origin, a capture length, and a capture direction which is perpendicular to the planes. Outside the space between the planes, the model is not deformed."], "extent": [661, 899]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["Deformation is relative to the capture region ", {"type": "q", "text": ["spine"]}, " (the vector from the origin). For example, if the capture region vector is off-center from your model, when you twist the model it will twist around the capture region vector, creating a spiral effect."], "extent": [899, 1156]}, {"type": "video_group", "body": [{"ext": null, "type": "video", "indent": 0, "role": "item", "extent": [1156, 1164], "body": [], "container": true, "attrs": {"src": "/videos/bend.mp4"}}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}]}, {"level": 2, "id": "howto", "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["How to"], "extent": [1964, 1985], "body": [{"type": "task_group", "body": [{"ext": null, "type": "task", "indent": 0, "text": [" Use Bend tool from the shelf"], "role": "item", "extent": [1985, 2024], "body": [{"type": "ord_group", "body": [{"blevel": 6, "type": "ord", "indent": 4, "text": ["Select the faces you want to deform."], "extent": [2024, 2068]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "ord", "indent": 4, "text": ["On the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Deform"]}, " shelf tab, click the ", {"scheme": "Icon", "value": "SOP/twist", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/SOP/twist"}, " Twist, ", {"scheme": "Icon", "value": "SHELF/twist_bend", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/SHELF/twist_bend"}, " Bend, or ", {"scheme": "Icon", "value": "SHELF/twist_linear_taper", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/SHELF/twist_linear_taper"}, " Linear Taper tool."], "extent": [2068, 2222]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "ord", "indent": 4, "text": ["The tool asks you to click two points to define the capture region."], "extent": [2222, 2297], "body": [{"type": "bullet_group", "body": [{"blevel": 10, "type": "bullet", "indent": 8, "text": ["To start with an axis-aligned region fitted to the selection, just press ", {"keys": ["Enter"], "type": "keys", "text": null}, " instead of clicking points."], "extent": [2297, 2419]}, {"blevel": 10, "type": "bullet", "indent": 8, "text": ["If you want to define a custom or non-axis-aligned capture region, use the view options menu to switch to an Orthographic view, then click at the ", {"type": "em", "text": ["start"]}, " of the capture region, then click at the ", {"type": "em", "text": ["end"]}, "."], "extent": [2419, 2632], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 12, "text": [{"scheme": "Image", "value": "/images/ui/viewport_menus_anno.png", "type": "img", "text": ""}], "extent": [2632, 2688]}], "container": true}], "container": true}], "container": true}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "ord", "indent": 4, "text": ["See how to use the handles below."], "extent": [2688, 2729]}], "container": true}], "container": true}, {"ext": null, "type": "task", "indent": 0, "text": [" Use Bend tool from the network"], "role": "item", "extent": [2729, 2773], "body": [{"type": "ord_group", "body": [{"blevel": 6, "type": "ord", "indent": 4, "text": ["Use the ", {"keys": ["Tab"], "type": "keys", "text": null}, " menu to add a Bend node to the network."], "extent": [2773, 2836]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "ord", "indent": 4, "text": ["Edit the Capture parameters to set the capture region."], "extent": [2836, 2898], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["If you create the node in the network, unlike using the shelf tool in the viewport, it doesn\u2019t do anything to fit the capture region to the input geometry."], "extent": [2898, 3064]}], "container": true}], "container": true}], "container": true}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}]}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Shelf tools"], "extent": [3064, 3082], "body": [{"level": 3, "id": "squash", "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Squash and stretch"], "extent": [3082, 3119], "body": [{"type": "summary", "indent": 0, "text": ["Sets up a Bend deformer on the selected geometry, set to show volume-preserving squash-and-stretch handles."], "extent": [3119, 3235]}]}, {"level": 3, "id": "taper", "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Taper"], "extent": [3235, 3257], "body": [{"type": "summary", "indent": 0, "text": ["Sets up a Bend deformer on the selected geometry, set to show tapering handles."], "extent": [3257, 3345]}]}, {"level": 3, "id": "bend", "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Bend"], "extent": [3345, 3365], "body": [{"type": "summary", "indent": 0, "text": ["Sets up a Bend deformer on the selected geometry, set to show bend handles."], "extent": [3365, 3449]}]}, {"level": 3, "id": "twist", "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Twist"], "extent": [3449, 3471], "body": [{"type": "summary", "indent": 0, "text": ["Sets up a Bend deformer on the selected geometry, set to show twist handles."], "extent": [3471, 3557]}]}]}, {"level": 2, "id": "handles", "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Handles"], "extent": [3557, 3581], "body": [{"type": "table", "thead": [], "body": [{"type": "row", "body": [{"type": "cell", "indent": 0, "text": [{"type": "strong", "text": ["Bend"]}, " "], "role": "td", "extent": [3581, 3591], "container": true, "attrs": {"width": "15%"}}, {"type": "cell", "indent": 4, "text": [{"scheme": "Image", "value": "/images/nodes/sop/bend_bend_before.jpg", "type": "img", "text": ""}, " ", {"scheme": "Image", "value": "/images/nodes/sop/bend_bend_after.jpg", "type": "img", "text": ""}, " "], "role": "td", "extent": [3608, 3707], "container": true, "attrs": {"width": "25%"}}, {"type": "cell", "role": "td", "body": [{"type": "bullet_group", "body": [{"blevel": 10, "type": "bullet", "indent": 8, "text": ["To show the Bend handle, turn on the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Enable"]}, " checkbox in the Bend section of the parameters."], "extent": [3728, 3835], "body": [{"type": "box_group", "body": [{"ext": null, "type": "box", "indent": 12, "text": [" Bend handle"], "role": "item", "extent": [3835, 3865], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 16, "text": [{"scheme": "Image", "value": "/images/nodes/sop/bend_handle_bend.jpg", "type": "img", "text": ""}], "extent": [3865, 3929]}], "container": true}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}], "container": true}, {"blevel": 10, "type": "bullet", "indent": 8, "text": ["Use the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Up vector control"]}, " to set the bend axis."], "extent": [3929, 3992]}, {"blevel": 10, "type": "bullet", "indent": 8, "text": ["You can set the bend angle using the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Up vector angle"]}, " in the parameters."], "extent": [3992, 4079], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 12, "text": [{"scheme": "Image", "value": "/images/nodes/sop/bend_handle_bend_angle.jpg", "type": "img", "text": ""}], "extent": [4079, 4145]}], "container": true}, {"blevel": 10, "type": "bullet", "indent": 8, "text": ["Drag the arc left or right to bend in one direction or the other. This is the same as modifying the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Bend"]}, " parameter."], "extent": [4145, 4276]}], "container": true}, {"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Distances between points are preserved along the spine. Distances on the inside of the bend shrink, and distances on the outside of the bend grow."], "extent": [4276, 4432]}]}], "divider": false}, {"type": "row", "body": [{"type": "cell", "indent": 0, "text": [{"type": "strong", "text": ["Twist"]}, " "], "role": "td", "extent": [4432, 4442], "container": true}, {"type": "cell", "indent": 4, "text": [{"scheme": "Image", "value": "/images/nodes/sop/bend_twist_before.jpg", "type": "img", "text": ""}, " ", {"scheme": "Image", "value": "/images/nodes/sop/bend_twist_after.jpg", "type": "img", "text": ""}, " "], "role": "td", "extent": [4442, 4543], "container": true}, {"type": "cell", "role": "td", "body": [{"type": "bullet_group", "body": [{"blevel": 10, "type": "bullet", "indent": 8, "text": ["To show the Twist handle, turn on the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Enable"]}, " checkbox in the Twist section of the parameters."], "extent": [4543, 4661], "body": [{"type": "box_group", "body": [{"ext": null, "type": "box", "indent": 12, "text": [" Twist handle"], "role": "item", "extent": [4661, 4692], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 16, "text": [{"scheme": "Image", "value": "/images/nodes/sop/bend_handle_twist.jpg", "type": "img", "text": ""}], "extent": [4692, 4757]}], "container": true}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}], "container": true}, {"blevel": 10, "type": "bullet", "indent": 8, "text": ["Drag the ring left or right to twist in one direction or the other. This is the same as modifying the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Twist"]}, " parameter."], "extent": [4757, 4891]}], "container": true}]}], "divider": false}, {"type": "row", "body": [{"type": "cell", "indent": 0, "text": [{"type": "strong", "text": ["Length Scale"]}, " "], "role": "td", "extent": [4891, 4908], "container": true}, {"type": "cell", "indent": 4, "text": [{"scheme": "Image", "value": "/images/nodes/sop/bend_length_scale_before.jpg", "type": "img", "text": ""}, " ", {"scheme": "Image", "value": "/images/nodes/sop/bend_length_scale_after.jpg", "type": "img", "text": ""}, " "], "role": "td", "extent": [4908, 5023], "container": true}, {"type": "cell", "role": "td", "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["This lets you scale the model along the length of the capture region, with optional ", {"type": "q", "text": ["squash and stretch"]}, " volume preservation."], "extent": [5023, 5167]}, {"type": "bullet_group", "body": [{"blevel": 10, "type": "bullet", "indent": 8, "text": ["To show the Length handle, turn on the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Enable"]}, " checkbox in the Length Scale section of the parameters."], "extent": [5167, 5284], "body": [{"type": "box_group", "body": [{"ext": null, "type": "box", "indent": 12, "text": [" Length Scale handle"], "role": "item", "extent": [5284, 5322], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 16, "text": [{"scheme": "Image", "value": "/images/nodes/sop/bend_handle_length.jpg", "type": "img", "text": ""}], "extent": [5322, 5388]}], "container": true}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}], "container": true}, {"blevel": 10, "type": "bullet", "indent": 8, "text": ["Drag the handle to scale the along the length of the capture region. This is the same as modifying the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Length scale"]}, " parameter."], "extent": [5388, 5530]}, {"blevel": 10, "type": "bullet", "indent": 8, "text": ["Turn on ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Preserve volume"]}, " to get squash/stretch as you scale the model down/up."], "extent": [5530, 5623]}], "container": true}]}], "divider": false}, {"type": "row", "body": [{"type": "cell", "indent": 0, "text": [{"type": "strong", "text": ["Taper"]}, " "], "role": "td", "extent": [5623, 5633], "container": true}, {"type": "cell", "indent": 4, "text": [{"scheme": "Image", "value": "/images/nodes/sop/bend_taper_before.jpg", "type": "img", "text": ""}, " ", {"scheme": "Image", "value": "/images/nodes/sop/bend_taper_after.jpg", "type": "img", "text": ""}, " "], "role": "td", "extent": [5633, 5734], "container": true}, {"type": "cell", "role": "td", "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["This lets you scale in/out at a ", {"type": "em", "text": ["midpoint"]}, " and the ", {"type": "em", "text": ["end"]}, " of the capture region."], "extent": [5734, 5824]}, {"type": "bullet_group", "body": [{"blevel": 10, "type": "bullet", "indent": 8, "text": ["To show the Taper handle, turn on the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Enable"]}, " checkbox in the Taper section of the parameters."], "extent": [5824, 5933], "body": [{"type": "box_group", "body": [{"ext": null, "type": "box", "indent": 12, "text": [" Taper handle"], "role": "item", "extent": [5933, 5964], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 16, "text": [{"scheme": "Image", "value": "/images/nodes/sop/bend_handle_taper.jpg", "type": "img", "text": ""}], "extent": [5964, 6029]}], "container": true}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}], "container": true}, {"blevel": 10, "type": "bullet", "indent": 8, "text": ["Drag the plane at the end to scale the end of the capture region in/out. This is the same as modifying the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Taper"]}, " parameter."], "extent": [6029, 6168]}, {"blevel": 10, "type": "bullet", "indent": 8, "text": ["Drag the plane at the midpoint to scale the middle of the capture region in/out. This is the same as modifying the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Squish"]}, " parameter."], "extent": [6168, 6316]}, {"blevel": 10, "type": "bullet", "indent": 8, "text": ["Drag the arrows above/below the midpoint plane to move the ", {"type": "q", "text": ["midpoint"]}, " along the length of the capture region. This is the same as modifying the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Squish pivot"]}, " parameter."], "extent": [6316, 6499]}, {"blevel": 10, "type": "bullet", "indent": 8, "text": ["Use the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Mode"]}, " parameter to choose whether the scales blend with the rest of the model ", {"type": "strong", "text": ["linearly"]}, " or ", {"type": "strong", "text": ["smoothly"]}, "."], "extent": [6499, 6625]}, {"blevel": 10, "type": "bullet", "indent": 8, "text": ["See ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Enable ramp"]}, " below for even more control over scaling along the length."], "extent": [6625, 6716]}], "container": true}]}], "divider": false}]}]}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Scaling effects using masks"], "extent": [6716, 6750], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["You can scale the effect of the deformations (globally and per-deformation) using mask attributes on the geometry. You can create useful mask attributes using ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/distancealonggeometry", "type": "link", "text": ["Distance Along Geometry"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/distancealonggeometry"}, ", ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/distancefromgeometry", "type": "link", "text": ["Distance From Geometry"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/distancefromgeometry"}, ", and ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/distancefromtarget", "type": "link", "text": ["Distance from Point"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/distancefromtarget"}, "."], "extent": [6750, 7080]}, {"type": "bullet_group", "body": [{"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": ["The ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Mask"]}, " parameter at the top lets you scale all deformation globally using a mask attribute."], "extent": [7080, 7181]}, {"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": ["Different controls for the various deformation types allow you to scale the control value by a mask attribute. Change the ", {"type": "q", "text": ["No Scaling"]}, " pop-up menu to ", {"type": "q", "text": ["Scale by Attribute"]}, ", then specify the mask attribute name."], "extent": [7181, 7395]}], "container": true}]}, {"level": 1, "id": "parameters", "container": true, "type": "parameters_section", "indent": 0, "role": "section", "extent": [7395, 7407], "body": [{"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Group"], "extent": [7407, 7415], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Subset of geometry to deform. Leave this blank to deform all input geometry."], "extent": [7415, 7497]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Primitives with transforms (such as spheres, packed primitives, and volumes) will be transformed if their base point is. "], "extent": [7497, 7624]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Group Type"], "extent": [7624, 7636], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["While this node deforms points, you can select different group types (such as primitive groups or vertex groups). The node automatically converts the selection to points."], "extent": [7636, 7812]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Mask"], "extent": [7812, 7818], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["When the pop-up menu is set to ", {"type": "q", "text": ["Mask on"]}, ", use this point attribute to ", {"type": "q", "text": ["scale"]}, " all deformation using a ", {"type": "q", "text": ["mask"]}, " attribute. Points where the attribute is ", {"type": "code", "text": ["0"]}, " are not deformed, points where the attribute is ", {"type": "code", "text": ["1"]}, " are fully deformed, with linear interpolation in between."], "extent": [7818, 8087]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["You can create useful mask attributes using ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/distancealonggeometry", "type": "link", "text": ["Distance Along Geometry"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/distancealonggeometry"}, ", ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/distancefromgeometry", "type": "link", "text": ["Distance From Geometry"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/distancefromgeometry"}, ", and ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/distancefromtarget", "type": "link", "text": ["Distance from Point"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/distancefromtarget"}, "."], "extent": [8087, 8305]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Click the paint icon to the right of the text field to paint the mask attribute directly in the viewport."], "extent": [8305, 8417]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Deformation"], "extent": [8417, 8435], "body": [{"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Enable Deformation"], "extent": [8435, 8456], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Globally turn all deformation on/off. This is useful when you want to adjust the capture parameters and want to see the original input geometry."], "extent": [8456, 8606]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Limit Deformation to Capture Region"], "extent": [8606, 8643], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["When this is on, the deformation only occurs within the capture region (this is the default). When this is off, it extends the deformation beyond the end of the capture region to the end of the model."], "extent": [8643, 8849]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["A global squash/stretch works best with this parameter ", {"type": "strong", "text": ["off"]}, ", since the squishing will be performed uniformly rather than tapering off to the capture bounds."], "extent": [8849, 9012]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Deform in Both Directions"], "extent": [9012, 9039], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Apply bend symmetrically across the capture origin, in both the forward and backward directions."], "extent": [9039, 9141]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": [{"scheme": "Image", "value": "/images/nodes/sop/bend_both.jpg", "type": "img", "text": ""}], "extent": [9141, 9187]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}, {"level": 3, "type": "sep", "indent": 0, "text": [" Bend "], "extent": [9187, 9200]}, {"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Enable"], "extent": [9200, 9209], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Perform bend deformation, show the Bend handle in the viewport."], "extent": [9209, 9278]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Mode"], "extent": [9278, 9284], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Whether the amount of bend is an ", {"type": "em", "text": ["angle"]}, ", or a ", {"type": "em", "text": ["direction"]}, " that the capture spine capture should end up pointing along."], "extent": [9284, 9409]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Bend"], "extent": [9409, 9415], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["When ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Mode"]}, " is ", {"type": "q", "text": ["Angle"]}, ", the angle in degrees to bend. You can make this over 180 to bend something over itself multiple times."], "extent": [9415, 9549]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Goal Direction"], "extent": [9549, 9565], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["When ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Mode"]}, " is ", {"type": "q", "text": ["Direction"]}, ", bend the capture region spine to end up pointing in this direction."], "extent": [9565, 9668]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Up Vector Control"], "extent": [9668, 9687], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The bend is always perpendicular to the capture axis, but this\n    specifies what orientation it should use."], "extent": [9687, 9801]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Up Vector"], "extent": [9801, 9812], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The up vector to use."], "extent": [9812, 9839]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Up Vector Angle"], "extent": [9839, 9856], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Angle (in degrees) to rotate the up vector around the capture spine."], "extent": [9856, 9931]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}, {"level": 3, "type": "sep", "indent": 0, "text": [" Twist "], "extent": [9931, 9945]}, {"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Enable"], "extent": [9945, 9954], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Perform twist deformation, show the Twist handle in the viewport."], "extent": [9954, 10025]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Twist"], "extent": [10025, 10032], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Angle in degrees to twist around the capture axis. This can be more than 360 degrees. The total twist is distributed evenly along the length of the capture region."], "extent": [10032, 10201]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Continuous Twist in Both Directions"], "extent": [10201, 10238], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["When ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Deform in Both Directions"]}, " is enabled, will cause the continued deformation\n    in the symmetric direction to be a continuation of the twist in the foreward direction."], "extent": [10238, 10419]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}, {"level": 3, "type": "sep", "indent": 0, "text": [" Length Scale "], "extent": [10419, 10440]}, {"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Enable"], "extent": [10440, 10449], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Perform length scaling, show the Length handle in the viewport."], "extent": [10449, 10518]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Preserve Volume"], "extent": [10518, 10535], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Do ", {"type": "q", "text": ["squash and stretch"]}, ": as you scale the length, apply an inverse perpendicular scale, so lengthening the model makes it skinny, and shortening the model makes it bulge. (Because this is applied smoothly, it is not technically accurate volume preservation). When ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Limit deformation to capture region"]}, " is on, the scaling falls off at the ends of the capture region."], "extent": [10535, 10908]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Length Scale"], "extent": [10908, 10922], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Scale the length of the captured geometry by this factor."], "extent": [10922, 10986]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}, {"level": 3, "type": "sep", "indent": 0, "text": [" Taper "], "extent": [10986, 11000]}, {"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Enable"], "extent": [11000, 11009], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Perform tapering, show the Taper handle in the viewport."], "extent": [11009, 11071]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Mode"], "extent": [11071, 11077], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Whether to blend linearly between taper scales, or smoothly (ease-in and ease-out)."], "extent": [11077, 11166]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Taper"], "extent": [11166, 11173], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The amount to scale the end of the capture region."], "extent": [11173, 11229]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Squish"], "extent": [11229, 11237], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The amount to scale the ", {"type": "q", "text": ["midpoint"]}, " of the capture region. You can move this scale between the start and end of the region using the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Squish pivot"]}, " parameter below."], "extent": [11237, 11408]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Squish Pivot"], "extent": [11408, 11422], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The position of the ", {"type": "q", "text": ["midpoint"]}, " scale along the length of the capture region, where ", {"type": "code", "text": ["0"]}, " means the start of the region, ", {"type": "code", "text": ["0.5"]}, " is halfway, and ", {"type": "code", "text": ["1.0"]}, " is the end."], "extent": [11422, 11585]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Enable Ramp"], "extent": [11585, 11598], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Lets you apply an arbitrary number of taper scales along the length of the capture region, controlled by a ramp."], "extent": [11598, 11716]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Profile"], "extent": [11716, 11725], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["When ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Enable ramp"]}, " is on, the horizontal axis represents the length of the capture region (start on the left, end on the right). At each point across, the value represents the amount of scaling (where ", {"type": "code", "text": ["0.5"]}, " means ", {"type": "q", "text": ["no scaling"]}, ", values greater than ", {"type": "code", "text": ["0.5"]}, " scale out, values less than ", {"type": "code", "text": ["0.5"]}, " scale in). Note that you can set a value for a point above ", {"type": "code", "text": ["1.0"]}, " using the parameters below the ramp."], "extent": [11725, 12121]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": [{"scheme": "Image", "value": "/images/nodes/sop/bend_taper_ramp.jpg", "type": "img", "text": ""}], "extent": [12121, 12172]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": [{"scheme": "Image", "value": "/images/nodes/sop/bend_taper_ramp_after.jpg", "type": "img", "text": ""}], "extent": [12172, 12230]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}, {"level": 3, "type": "sep", "indent": 0, "text": [" Capture "], "extent": [12230, 12246]}, {"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Set Capture Region"], "extent": [12246, 12267], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Click this, then click two points in an orthographic viewport to define the capture region. This is the same as choosing the points when ", {"scheme": null, "value": "#howto", "type": "link", "text": ["using the shelf tool"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/bend#howto", "fragment": "#howto"}, "."], "extent": [12267, 12444]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Capture Origin"], "extent": [12444, 12460], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The center of the source capture plane."], "extent": [12460, 12505]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Capture Direction"], "extent": [12505, 12524], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The normal of the capture planes, and the direction pointing to the destination capture plane from the source."], "extent": [12524, 12640]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Capture Length"], "extent": [12640, 12656], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Controls the region of space that receives the partial transforms. Must not be zero in length."], "extent": [12656, 12756]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Output Attribute"], "extent": [12756, 12774], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["When this is on, create this point float attribute on the output geometry. The attribute will have ", {"type": "code", "text": ["0"]}, " on points that were not deformed, and ", {"type": "code", "text": ["1"]}, " on points that were fully deformed. This may be useful for visualizing the amount of deformation in different parts of the model."], "extent": [12774, 13055]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}]}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Attributes"], "extent": [13055, 13072], "body": [{"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Use Rest Positions"], "extent": [13072, 13093], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["If this is on, and the second input is connected, use the point positions in the second input to compute which points are in the capture region. If this is on and the second input is ", {"type": "em", "text": ["not"]}, " connected, use a ", {"type": "code", "text": ["rest"]}, " point attribute if present (this should be a 3float attribute containing the ", {"type": "q", "text": ["rest"]}, " position of each point). If this is on but no ", {"type": "code", "text": ["rest"]}, " attribute exists, the node creates it from the initial point positions. If this is off, the node uses the point positions as they are in the input."], "extent": [13093, 13596]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Attributes to Transform"], "extent": [13596, 13621], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["A space-separated list of names and/or patterns. Attributes whose names match are transformed along with the point positions. The node uses each attribute\u2019s type info to transform it properly (as points, vectors, or normals)."], "extent": [13621, 13852]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["If you change this from the default (", {"type": "code", "text": ["*"]}, ", all attributes), make sure ", {"type": "code", "text": ["P"]}, " (point positions) is on the list unless for some reason you want to transform other attributes but not actually deform the geometry."], "extent": [13852, 14063]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Recompute Affected Normals"], "extent": [14063, 14091], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Recomputes normals of polygons that have both transformed and untransformed points."], "extent": [14091, 14180]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["If you're transforming the full geometry or all connected components, this setting is irrelevant. It only matters if you deform part but not all of a connected piece."], "extent": [14180, 14352]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["This does nothing if ", {"type": "code", "text": ["P"]}, " is not listed/matched in ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Attributes to transform"]}, "."], "extent": [14352, 14436]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Preserve Normal Length"], "extent": [14436, 14460], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Normal lengths remain unaffected."], "extent": [14460, 14500]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}]}], "text": "Parameters"}, {"level": 1, "id": "inputs", "container": true, "type": "inputs_section", "indent": 0, "role": "section", "extent": [14500, 14508], "body": [{"type": "dt_group", "body": [{"type": "dt", "indent": 0, "text": ["Geometry to Bend"], "extent": [14508, 14527], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Can be any geometry, including NURBS and Beziers, but should have enough points for deformation to modify."], "extent": [14527, 14639]}], "container": true}, {"type": "dt", "indent": 0, "text": ["Rest Geometry"], "extent": [14639, 14654], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["If connected, the node uses this to determine where points are in the capture region. This is useful if you're stacking Bends and you don\u2019t want the capture to change as a result of upstream operations."], "extent": [14654, 14863]}], "container": true}], "container": true}], "text": "Inputs"}, {"level": 1, "id": "related", "container": true, "type": "related_section", "indent": 0, "role": "section", "extent": [14863, 14872], "body": [{"type": "bullet_group", "body": [{"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/deformationwrangle", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/deformationwrangle"}], "extent": [14872, 14905]}, {"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/pointdeform", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/pointdeform"}], "extent": [14905, 14933]}], "container": true}], "text": "Related"}], "title": ["Bend"], "summary": ["Applies deformations to captured geometry such as bend, twist, taper, and squash/stretch."]}